result.execSummary:
Gabriel Urrutia was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Gabriel Urrutia was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Gabriel Urrutia in court with attorney Brandon Kuhl. Defendant Gabriel Urrutia in custody. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

1:37 p.m.  Court calls the case. 

Atty Constable makes statements.  Has been informed the defendant would now like to waive his right to extradition.  Paperwork has been provided to the defendant to sign. 
Court questions Atty Kuhl. 
Atty Kuhl concurs.  
Court questions the defendant. 
Defendant concurs. 

BY THE COURT: Defendant has signed the waiver of extradition document here in open court with his attorney present and upon the advice of his counsel.  Court has witnessed his signature and Court now signs the document as well.  Defendant has exercised the right to counsel.  Court finds the defendant is freely, voluntarily, knowingly and with the advice of counsel, waiving his right to extradition.  He will return to Illinois to the probation department where he is wanted.

Court retains the original and returns the copies to the prosecutor for distribution.
Extradition hearing on January 29, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Extradition hearing on January 22, 2015 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Gabriel Urrutia in court, in custody. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

11:21 AM Court calls case.
Atty Constable states appearances.

Defendant appears without counsel.

Atty Constable states that Defendant wishes to fight extradition.
State has filed a fugitive from justice file and is seeking to work with Illinois. 

Defendant speaks english.
Address of Defendant is verified.
Defendant does not work.

Court reviews the file.
Defendant has Court today at 1:30, has counsel for that case. 

Court addresses Defendant as to right to bond in extradition.
Defendant has bond on his other case.
Defendant has been living in Portage County for the past 2 to 3 months.

Defendant previously lived with his girlfriend. 
Girlfriend's aunt has offered a place to stay for the Defendant.

Court continues questioning Defendant for clarifications.

Aggravated driving under the influence is the charge in Illinois.

Court will schedule this for an extradition hearing.

Defendant is on probation for OWI case in Illinois.

Court advises Defendant to talk with his attorney on his other matter to see if they will represent the Defendant on this matter.  Extradition hearing scheduled for January 22, 2015 at 11:00 am.
